@dorodnic Fedora kernels follow mainline rather than being frozen to whatever was stable when the distro release occurred. F25 kernel started on 4.9 (iirc) and recently moved from 4.10 to 4.11. The extra pixel format introduced between 4.9 and 4.10 in include/uapi/linux/videodev2.h makes the existing F25 patch for this file fail to apply. Patch also complains about two other patches applying at different lines than expected (but they apply and work) so I updated the line numbers in the diffs.

I understand Fedora is not supported, but it's useful for me and annoying when a patch fails to apply even though it's obvious to a human what should have happened.

I (Frans Gifford) agree to the terms of the Intel® RealSense™ Cross Platform API CLA but point out that the contributed change relates to a patch on GPLv2 Linux kernel code so I doubt I actually hold any copyright on it.

[Realsense Customer Engineering Team Comment] 
