It's not actually anything to do with pybind11 (or even Eigen, for that matter): the default `std::vector` allocator can't allocate or destroy a `const` value, hence the compilation failures.  This fails in the same way:

```C++
#include <vector>

int main() {
    std::vector<const int> foo;
}
```

Dropping the `const` from the vector type will fix it.

